item.title: Banks not working
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

Yeah, okay. This is exactly what I thought. You need to find the text id that is right there. There should be one.
Open the bank and then use this command:

		if(playerCommand.equalsIgnoreCase("flushids")){
			for(int i = 0; i < 30000; i++){
				c.getPA().sendFrame126(""+i, i);
			}
			c.sendMessage("Done.");
		}

It may freeze your client or something, or look like it isn’t doing anything, but just wait till it says done in the chat box.

item.title: Banks not working
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

lol space:

So, the server I have created pretty much from scratch with a few models and stuff ripped from other servers, I can’t seem to figure out what is wrong with the bank. It opens it. Everything is A OK. But theres no X to get out of the bank. I can’t seem to figure it out. Anyone have suggestions?

Manually add the sprite via RSInterface and your cache. Or see if there is a text button that is supposed to be there but isn’t because someone cleared the id by looping through a few thousand ID’s with a for loop and using sendFrame126 (or whatever you use to send packet 126).
